	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f102470224880954>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=12068&mid=102470224880954>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=12068&mid=102470224880954>RE: How to craft</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=12068&mid=102470224880954#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 21st 7:40 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=85584><span id=Sage>barfly</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>167 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.75]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Get two shade silks that drop from Shak Dratha in Shadeweaver's Thicket, and combine in loom or sewing kit (never fails, trivial at tailoring skill 15).&nbsp;&nbsp;Results in a shade silk swatch.<br><br>Combine swatch in sewing kit or loom with the appropriate pattern to get the armor piece (note: 2 swatches are required for pants and robe). Trivial at skill level of 36.<br><br>Basically the same process as making raw silk armor on Norrath (can also use shade silks for cured shade silk armor -- not sure about Wu's though). Same AC as raw silk armor, but shade silk has additional stats -- nothing to be overjoyed with, but what do you expect with newbie armor.<br><br>UPDATE (June 29, 2002)<br>Made the following items with shade silk:<br>Collar (AC 2 CHA+1)<br>Mantle (AC 2 WIS+1)<br>Cap (AC 3 INT+1)<br>Gloves (AC 3 DEX+1)<br>Sandals (AC 3 STA+1)<br>Robe (AC 6 AGI+1)<br><br>Robe is a nice dark grey (almost black), with black embroidery along the sides and down the front... at least that's how it looks on my gnome.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Jun 28 22:10:55 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
